dismissalText.commentary: Dwayne Smith c Hussey b McKay 43 (63b 2x4 1x6 86m) SR: 68.25

dismissalComment.html: terrific terrific catch! Hussey's pulled off the spectacular! Smith heaves the ball towards cow corner, Hussey sprints from long-on, he covers about 40 meters to his right at top speed before diving full length and taking the catch inches from the ground

dismissalText.commentary: Narsingh Deonarine lbw b Johnson 23 (36b 5x4 0x6 57m) SR: 63.88

dismissalComment.html: on the middle stump and hitting the leg stump or is it? Bowden certainly thinks so as Deonarine who was looking good has to go. There is an air of doubt around the dismissal as Bowden took his own sweet time in giving the decision and then walked over to the square leg umpire to discuss about it

dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin c Haddin b Watson 30 (42b 4x4 0x6 63m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: the bowling change works! Watson bowls it dead straight on the channel outside off, the ball holds its line and Ramdin fishes outside the off stump with  a half stride forward, thin edge and Haddin's good outing continues

commentTextItems.html: another excellent pull shot, wrong line and that disappears past square

commentPostTextItems.html: So that makes it 2-0 in Australia's favour. Ponting seals the win with a pull over square leg to a long hop. Bollinger is the Man of the Match. Thanks for tuning in today. Do come back and see us for game three on February 12. Bye for now!

commentTextItems.html: leans into a drive but cannot beat the man at cover
down the pads, Clarke shuffles and works it away for a single
back of a length on off stump and Ponting turns it to midwicket

headshotImage.caption: Ricky Ponting player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.longCaption: Narsingh Deonarine player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: uses his crease to counter the inswing with a flowing push to long-on
on the pads, turned away straight to midwicket
bit shorter, back goes Ponting to force it to the man at cover
comes across and whips the ball out to deep midwicket
onto the front foot and driving through to point
slides way down the leg side
marginally short and Ponting rocks back to pull over midwicket and up comes his half-century in good time

commentTextItems.html: tossed up, driven down the ground
no turn, gets across and pushes to midwicket
better length and Clarke defends off the back foot
again comes out and clips the ball away

commentPreTextItems.html: Ponting has turned it on in the batting Powerplay. Fun to watch. Here's Deonarine.

commentTextItems.html: tossed up, Ponting on-drives the ball to midwicket
now he slashes at one pitched up outside off and edges to third man

commentTextItems.html: maximum! Excellent timing from Ponting, pulling off the front foot and getting it over deep backward square leg, he just picked the length and used the wrists
walks across toward off again and brushes the ball to square leg
takes on the short ball with a lovely pirouette, pulling in front of square

dismissalText.commentary: Chris Gayle lbw b Bollinger 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: ball 1 strike 1! Right on target is Doug Bollinger, gets some late movement inwards and the ball straightens, lands on a good length and thuds his pads in line with the off stump, Gayle was too lazy in getting his bat down on time and he played down the wrong line

dismissalText.commentary: Travis Dowlin c Haddin b McKay 2 (16b 0x4 0x6 18m) SR: 12.5

dismissalComment.html: error in judgement outside the off stump, McKay lands it just a touch wide outside the off stump and he gets forward and shapes to let it go to the keeper, but the ball brushes the face of the bat and Haddin and the rest know it

dismissalText.commentary: Runako Morton lbw b Bollinger 4 (11b 0x4 0x6 24m) SR: 36.36

dismissalComment.html: tumbling like pins here, excellent delivery there, lands on a good length on middle and straightens a bit, Morton gets a touch forward but he's beaten for pace and gets hit on the pads in line with off and middle

headshotImage.caption: Doug Bollinger player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Doug Bollinger player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Lendl Simmons c Haddin b Bollinger 1 (4b 0x4 0x6 11m) SR: 25

dismissalComment.html: Doug's on fire! He bowls it on a fullish length and angles it just across the right-hander, Simmons is forced to play at it and he shapes to drive straight, the late movement catches the outside edge and another easy take for Haddin

dismissalText.commentary: Narsingh Deonarine lbw b Johnson 23 (36b 5x4 0x6 57m) SR: 63.88

dismissalComment.html: on the middle stump and hitting the leg stump or is it? Bowden certainly thinks so as Deonarine who was looking good has to go. There is an air of doubt around the dismissal as Bowden took his own sweet time in giving the decision and then walked over to the square leg umpire to discuss about it

dismissalText.commentary: Denesh Ramdin c Haddin b Watson 30 (42b 4x4 0x6 63m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: the bowling change works! Watson bowls it dead straight on the channel outside off, the ball holds its line and Ramdin fishes outside the off stump with  a half stride forward, thin edge and Haddin's good outing continues

dismissalText.commentary: Kieron Pollard c Johnson b Bollinger 32 (39b 3x4 0x6 48m) SR: 82.05

dismissalComment.html: caught!! Bollinger's done it in his comeback over! The ball was on a good length and pretty straight, Pollard tried to hit across the line towards mid-on but the angle of the ball - across him - forced it to hit the leading edge, Johnson settled under the catch at mid-off

headshotImage.caption: Nathan Hauritz player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Nathan Hauritz player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Nikita Miller c Marsh b Hauritz 6 (7b 1x4 0x6 11m) SR: 85.71

dismissalComment.html: caught! Miller tries to drive, he's beaten by flight and dip and spoons a catch to White at cover point, West indies are in danger of leaving a serious number of overs unused

dismissalText.commentary: Ravi Rampaul run out (Ponting) 18 (22b 3x4 0x6 35m) SR: 81.81

dismissalComment.html: direct hit! And it's Ponting! Rampaul jumps back to play a short ball and it goes towards point, Rampaul's deep in his crease when he starts running so Ponting has plenty of time to line up the stumps at the bowler's end and throw, he hits the top of middle

dismissalText.commentary: Dwayne Smith c Hussey b McKay 43 (63b 2x4 1x6 86m) SR: 68.25

dismissalComment.html: terrific terrific catch! Hussey's pulled off the spectacular! Smith heaves the ball towards cow corner, Hussey sprints from long-on, he covers about 40 meters to his right at top speed before diving full length and taking the catch inches from the ground

dismissalText.commentary: Shane Watson c Ramdin b Roach 53 (50b 7x4 2x6 65m) SR: 106

dismissalComment.html: thin little nick and Watson has to go! That pitches on just about the perfect length and forces Watson to push at it, and the wee bit of shape takes care of the rest

dismissalText.commentary: Shaun Marsh b Smith 27 (27b 3x4 1x6 37m) SR: 100

dismissalComment.html: chops it on! Marsh has been struggling against this angle across the stumps and has been caught between angling the bat and leaving, and he perishes trying to run one too close to the body, the ball takes the under-edge and hits the stumps
